Hello, 

I currently have an issue when decompressing DDS DXT1 image. Here is my code: 

```
const size_t _Size = m_pImage->GetWidth() * m_pImage->GetHeight() * 4;
unsigned char* _pData = new unsigned char[_Size];       
m_pImage->GetCompressedLevel(0).Decompress(_pData);  
_pFinalImage->SetData(_pData);
_pFinalImage->SavePNG("test.png");
delete[] _pData;
```

Here is how the produced image look like (using the mushroom texture): 
![test](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8931643/16926397/c0bb2ce0-4d28-11e6-95f2-b25bbca225cb.png)

DXT5 compression is working fine.

Am i doing something wrong here ?

This is a feature request. Currently incuding Urho3D is usually of this style

```
#include <Urho3D/Module/ClassName.h>
```

which requires me to grep alot of code to find the include I need.
