# Solution 2: Only modules

```
#include <Urho3D/Module.h>
```

This is a balance between 1 umbrella header for everything and the what is now. I see there is an umbrella header for each module but it is not clear if it's an umbrella header as it only includes a few items from that module. Judging on the samples source code it's not a proper umbrella header.
# Solution 3: Class Level

This is Similar to what c++ standard library does

```
#include <Urho3D/ClassName.h>
```

The complete opposite of umbrella header.

I like Solution 1 & 2 as they can be done together. Solution 3 is much too granular.

Thank you.

There is some problems with RigidBody2D 

for example when trying to SetLinearVelocity() during simulation on a moving body to attempt to change its velocity, it will work only once (or even never if you specify a 0,0 velocity)... 

```
void RigidBody2D::SetLinearVelocity(const Vector2& linearVelocity)
{
    b2Vec2 b2linearVelocity = ToB2Vec2(linearVelocity);
    if (bodyDef_.linearVelocity == b2linearVelocity)
        return;

    bodyDef_.linearVelocity = b2linearVelocity;

    if (body_)
        body_->SetLinearVelocity(b2linearVelocity);

    MarkNetworkUpdate();
}
```

because of :
if (bodyDef_.linearVelocity == b2linearVelocity)
        return;

bodyDef.linearVelocity does not reflect real body linearVelocity during simulation, and so it stay to the last manually set value and next time always return and never more affect body if value is the same that the previous one.

I think it's the same for others bodyDef properties... that don't reflect real body properties during simulation.

I suggest that the if and return statement are not needed and may be removed, what do you think ?

