I compiled Urho3D with `-Wall -Wextra -pedantic` to fix some of the more serious warnings.
- Removed a plaethora of commas at the end of enums
- Removed a plaethora of superfluous semi-colons
- Commented out unused variables
- Fixed ordering of a initializer lists (-Wreorder)

During this, I also discovered some minor WTFs and even discovered a bug.
### Strangeness 1

What is this? As far as I can see, `isASCII` is always true no matter what. The if statement will always evaluate to being false because `buffer[i]` is a (signed) const char.
Source/ThirdParty/Assimp/code/STLLoader.cpp:103

``` cpp
    bool isASCII( strncmp( buffer, "solid", 5 ) == 0 );
    if( isASCII ) {
        // A lot of importers are write solid even if the file is binary. So we have to check for ASCII-characters.
        if( fileSize >= 500 ) {
            isASCII = true;
            for( unsigned int i = 0; i < 500; i++ ) {
                if( buffer[ i ] > 127 ) { // warning: comparison is always false due to limited range of data type [-Wtype-limits]
